 \frac{a}{x}y'(x) + \frac{1}{2}y''(x) = 0 
a
z=y'
\frac{a}{x}z(x)+\frac{1}{2}z'(x)=0
z'=-\frac{2a}{x}z
\ln|z|=\int \frac{dz}{z} = \int -\frac{2a}{x}dx=-2a\ln|x|+C_0
y'=z=C_1x^{-2a}
y=\frac{C_1}{1-2a}x^{1-2a}+C_2
~y'=u \Rightarrow y''=u'~
\frac{1}{2}u'+\frac{a}{x}u=0 \Rightarrow \frac{1}{2}u'=\frac{-a}{x}u \Rightarrow \int \frac{du}{u} = -2a\int \frac {dx}{x}
x=0
2ay' + xy'' = 0
y'=v
y'' = v'
2av + xv' = 0
\frac{2a}{x} =- \frac{v'}{v}
2a\log{Cx} =-\log v
2a\log{Cx} =-\log v
{Kx^{-2a}} =y'
